<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,310,834,860]" box="[189,310,834,860]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,834,860]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,834,860]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1399,881,1120]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
The red, fleshy bristles at the petiole apex are an unusual character in Asian 
<taxonomicName box="[1098,1196,882,907]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1098,1196,882,907]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and demonstrate an alliance of this species with 
<taxonomicName authority="Jack (Jack 1822)" authorityName="Jack (Jack" authorityYear="1822" box="[560,916,916,943]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sublobata">
<emphasis box="[560,710,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. sublobata</emphasis>
Jack (
<bibRefCitation author="Jack W." box="[786,908,916,943]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref18405" refString="Jack W. 1822. Descriptions of Malayan plants. Malayan Miscellanies 2 (7): 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1822">Jack 1822</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hughes &amp; Girmansyah &amp; Ardi, 2015" authorityName="Hughes &amp; Girmansyah &amp; Ardi" authorityYear="2015" box="[975,1101,917,943]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluvialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[975,1101,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. fluvialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1109,1204,917,943]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Hughes &amp; Girmansyah &amp; Ardi, 2015" authorityName="Hughes &amp; Girmansyah &amp; Ardi" authorityYear="2015" box="[1217,1398,917,943]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="korthalsiana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1217,1398,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. korthalsiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,279,952,978]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs considerably from both in its larger, unlobed ovate-orbicular leaves (18–24 × 
<quantity box="[1275,1394,952,979]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="cm" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20 cm</quantity>
, 
<emphasis box="[189,209,988,1013]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">c.</emphasis>
12 × 
<quantity box="[278,351,987,1014]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="cm" value="12.0">12 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jack (Jack" authorityYear="1822" box="[389,538,987,1013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sublobata">
<emphasis box="[389,538,987,1013]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. sublobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and much larger inflorescences (
<emphasis box="[937,957,988,1013]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[965,1038,987,1014]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="cm" value="60.0">60 cm</quantity>
long with 
<emphasis box="[1165,1185,988,1013]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">c.</emphasis>
100 flowers 
<emphasis box="[1339,1398,988,1013]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">vs. c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[189,263,1022,1049]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="cm" value="15.0">15 cm</quantity>
long with 
<emphasis box="[393,413,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">c.</emphasis>
30 flowers in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jack (Jack" authorityYear="1822" box="[586,735,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sublobata">
<emphasis box="[586,735,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. sublobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The male flowers were described from sketches made by Irmscher in 
<collectingRegion box="[372,449,1058,1084]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Berlin</collectingRegion>
; the material is sparse and whether the flowers consistently have 2 tepals needs confirmation; the smaller size of the female flowers is probably due their immaturity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,324,1159,1185]" box="[189,324,1159,1185]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1159,1185]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1159,1185]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1398,1205,1302]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Named after the Dutch botanist Pieter W. Korthals [
<date box="[795,933,1205,1232]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1807" valueMax="1892">1807–1892</date>
] who was the first person to collect this species, with the specimens being later annotated by Miquel. The specimens collected by Beccari were chosen as the 
<typeStatus box="[353,404,1276,1302]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
as they had better fruiting material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
